# Code Generator System

## Two layers (same module contract)
- **`src/`** — compiler; follow `codegen-src` rule (`tools/verify_src_contract.py`).
- **`io/output/`** — generated runtime; follow `codegen-output` rule.

## Node (single source of truth)
Each node records: `semantic`, `function_name`, `io.in`, `io.out`, `role`, `topology`.

## Emission
- Composite → `render_init` template only (no LLM for `__init__.py`).
- Leaf → LLM + AST verify; function name must equal `function_name`.
- Leaf test → template `test_{function_name}.py` from typed io.
- Shared copy → re-verify stdlib-only before `register_leaf`.

## Topology templates
- SEQ: chain `ctx = child(ctx)` using named imports.
- ROUTER: dispatch on `ctx["meta"]["case"]` to child function.

## Do not
- Emit generic `def run()` in generated code.
- Skip `verify_code` on `__init__.py`.
- Register shared modules without stdlib import check.
- Add multi-function leaf modules under `src/` without nesting or splitting.
